    Apologies for the oversight. In order to write content to a file using write_file, you must provide both the destination path to create the file at, as well as the body of text or structured content to completely fill that file with.
    
    The proper function call syntax would look something like this in Hermes:
    
    {"arguments": {"path": "/home/user/newfile.txt", "content": "This is a new file, being written from scratch by write_file."}, "name": "write_file"}
    
    You'll specify the 'path' to create at, and then pass your full content string or structured data blob as the 'content'. 
    
    Anything but those two key fields will result in an error if submitted as the only parameters. So be sure you supply both a 'path' to overwrite, along with your 'content' to stuff into that file.
    
    Let me know if this clears things up or if you need any other help using write_file!
